## Architecture rules
- src/index.js is the production entry point. worker.js isOT deployed directly.
- All new business logic goes in src/ as focused modules.
- worker.js gets max one import + one route delegation per module. Nothing else.
- When touching any worker.js reference: extract logic into src/ at the same time.
- Never hardcode workspace_id, tenant_id, email addresses, or secret values.

## Deploy — never guess (wrong command = wasted work)
- `npm run deploy:full` — DEFAULT. Any change under dashboard/ (Vite build + R2 upload + Worker deploy).
- `npm run deploy` — Worker/API only (src/, worker.js backend changes). No R2 upload.
- `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler deploy -c wrangler.production.toml` — Worker-only one-liner.
- `npm run deploy:ingest` — Route map + D1 schema doc + memory ingest + Worker deploy.

## Sandbox is DISCONTINUED
- Never suggest deploy-sandbox.sh or promote-to-prod.sh — both are marked dangerous/discontinued.
- Deploy directly to production with npm run deploy:full.

## Dashboard build rules
- NEVER run cd dashboard
- Always usix dashboard run build OR npm run build:vite-only from repo root

CF Builds auto-deploys Worker on push to main. Does NOT upload R2 frontend bundle.
Run deploy:full locally when dashboard changes need to be live immediately.
